                <div id="project-surname">Print Design</div>
                <p>My final assignment for History of Graphic Design, taught by my Professor, <a blank="target" hfef="http://www.risd.edu/academics/graphic-design/faculty/Doug-Scott/">Doug Scott</a>, was to design a collapsable timeline highlighting a given famous Graphic Designer. I was given Bradbury Thompson. After reading <i>The Art of Graphic Design</i> to learn more about Bradbury, I was completely enthralled. The book, the work that lies within the pages, all masterful compositions of image and type, making the ardous task of designing and printing with a lithographic offset printer look like play.</p>
