        <section class="project">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="large-8 large-offset-2 columns">
                <p>Above is the cover of the final printed design. The cover was inspired by Bradbury's combination of "type and image", I wanted to begin by highlighting type, and then adding image with the opening of the pamphlet. To create this effect, I worked with my 3D foundations teacher <a target="blank" href="http://www.northeastern.edu/camd/artdesign/people/benjamin-caras/">Ben Caras</a> to lasercut out the letters in order to give the "keyhole" effect. This was a long and frustrating process where I learned the limitations of modern printers. However, after hours of bumping and nudging the design around the screen, we finally hit it perfectly. Below you can see the cover exposed from the outer laser-cut flap.
        </div>
